PRIVACY POLICY Last updated: 18th Feb, 2026

This Privacy Notice for Roam ("we", "us", or "our") describes how and why we access, collect, store, use, and share your personal information when you use our services, including when you download and use our mobile application (Roam).

This Privacy Notice is provided on behalf of the Government of Fiji.

Questions or concerns? Contact us at: 
leeshaprasad2555@gmail.com

1. WHAT INFORMATION DO WE COLLECT?

We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide when you register, including:

Names
Phone numbers
Email addresses
Usernames & passwords
Car number plate
We also automatically collect device data, location data (GPS), and push notification tokens when you use the app.

2. HOW DO WE PROCESS YOUR INFORMATION?

We process your information to:

Facilitate account creation and authentication
Deliver ride-booking services
Enable real-time driver-rider communication
Verify user identity and driver/vehicle details
Protect our services from fraud
Identify usage trends and improve the app
Send administrative notifications
3. WHEN AND WITH WHOM DO WE SHARE YOUR INFORMATION?

We may share your information:

During business transfers (mergers, acquisitions)
With other users as part of the ride-booking experience (e.g., your name and rating are visible to your driver/rider)
With third-party service providers (analytics, mapping, cloud hosting, payment processors, communication services) who are bound by data protection obligations
4. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

We use the following third-party services:

Google Maps Platform — location & routing
Firebase (Google) — authentication, database, cloud functions
Firebase Analytics & Crashlytics — usage analytics
Payment processors — secure fare processing
All third-party providers process your data in accordance with applicable data protection laws.

5. HOW LONG DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION?

Account information: retained while account is active; 180 days after deletion for fraud prevention
Device & location data: 90 days
Communication logs: 30 days
Car number plate: 7 days
After these periods, data is deleted or anonymized.

6. HOW DO WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION SAFE?

We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures. However, no internet transmission is 100% secure. You access the Services at your own risk and should only do so within a secure environment.

7. DO WE COLLECT INFORMATION FROM MINORS?

We do not knowingly collect data from children under 18. By using the Services, you confirm you are at least 18 years old. If we discover we have collected data from a minor, we will deactivate the account and delete the data promptly.

Contact: 
leeshaprasad2555@gmail.com

8. WHAT ARE YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS?

You have the right to:

Access your personal data
Correct inaccurate data
Request erasure ("Right to be Forgotten")
Restrict processing
Data portability
Object to processing
Withdraw consent at any time
To exercise these rights, contact us at 
leeshaprasad2555@gmail.com
 or use the "Delete Account" option in your Profile.

9. CONTROLS FOR DO-NOT-TRACK FEATURES

We do not currently respond to Do-Not-Track (DNT) browser signals as no uniform standard has been finalized. If a standard is adopted in the future, we will update this notice.

10. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS

Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than Fiji. We ensure appropriate safeguards, including Standard Contractual Clauses, are in place.

11. LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING

Consent — for specific purposes you agree to
Contractual Necessity — to provide the ride-booking service
Legal Obligation — to comply with applicable law
Legitimate Interests — fraud prevention, service improvement
12. DO WE MAKE UPDATES TO THIS NOTICE?

Yes. We may update this Privacy Notice periodically. The "Last updated" date at the top reflects the latest revision. Material changes will be communicated via in-app notification.

13. HOW CAN YOU CONTACT US?

